In the first city, one firefighter is proposing to save the doctor while in the heat of the moment.  It seems like a reasonable conclusion that he would choose the doctor.  The policy in city B seems a bit cold and calculated.  I'm not sure how safe I would feel as a citizen knowing that if I were trapped in a burning building, my life would not be worth saving because I'm not a doctor who can potentially save the world.  I think a decision made in the heat of the moment is more acceptable than a general policy.
